title: Ubuntu 18.10 -- TypeError: object of type 'NoneType' has no len()
body:
I am having issues to label multiple animals in DeepLabCut2.0: after I select the folder with the frames, I get the error below. As a consequence, I never load the frames which I would like to label. 

```
TypeError                                 Traceback (most recent call last)
~/Documents/DeepLabCut/deeplabcut/generate_training_dataset/multiple_individuals_labeling_toolbox.py in browseDir(self, event)
    666             uniquebodyparts,
    667             multianimalbodyparts,
--> 668         ) = auxfun_multianimal.extractindividualsandbodyparts(self.cfg)
    669 
    670         self.multibodyparts = multianimalbodyparts

~/Documents/DeepLabCut/deeplabcut/utils/auxfun_multianimal.py in extractindividualsandbodyparts(cfg)
     22 def extractindividualsandbodyparts(cfg):
     23     individuals = cfg["individuals"].copy()
---> 24     if len(cfg["uniquebodyparts"]) > 0:
     25         individuals.append("single")
     26     return individuals, cfg["uniquebodyparts"], cfg["multianimalbodyparts"]

TypeError: object of type 'NoneType' has no len()
```

Config: Ubuntu 18.04, DeepLabCut 2.2b6.
